In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney announces that on September 11, 2011, the President and Mrs. Obama will participate in commemorations at each of the three locations where many lives were lost. He also addresses questions about the debt legislation, the need for balance in future budget discussions, and the President's frustration with the political process. Carney emphasizes the importance of growing the economy and creating jobs, as well as the need for deficit reduction. He also discusses the United States' commitment to assisting Somalia during the famine crisis. Carney denies knowledge of any potential appointment for former New Jersey Governor Jon Corzine and states that the President's position on balanced budget amendments remains unchanged. Finally, Carney mentions the President's plans to focus on growing the economy and creating jobs in the coming weeks and months.